Supreme Court Temporarily Blocks Virginia Transgender Student From Boys Restroom
WASHINGTON—The Supreme Court on Wednesday temporarily blocked a Virginia transgender student who identifies as male from using the boys’ bathroom at his high school, giving local officials time to file a full appeal of a lower court ruling that sided with the high-school junior.
